MA-104 cells (1 × 105
 cells/well) were grown in 96-well plates for 48 h. The media were removed and replaced by new media containing serial dilutions of extracts under test. After incubation for 72 h, the media were discarded, and 5 μL of MTT (3-[4,5-dimethylthiozol-2-yl]-2,5-diphenyltetrazolium bromide; Sigma, St. Louis, MO) solution was added to each well. Plates were then incubated at 37 °C for 4 h. The solution was removed, and 100 μL of 0.04 M HCl-isopropanol was added to each well to dissolve formazan crystals (Fig. 1
). Using a microplate reader, the absorbance of each well was measured at 540 nm. After subtracting the background absorbance at 655 nm, the 50% cytotoxic concentration (CC50) of each extract was estimated by regression analysis.
